name: Joshua Wayne

deck: Only son of Alan Wayne and Catherine Van Derm as well as the founder of Wayne Chemical. Great-Grandfather of Batman
description: Kenneth Wayne is the only son of Alan and Catherine Wayne. He founded Wayne Chemical and continued the general growth of Wayne Enterprises by industrializing Gotham City. Kenneth wasn't as long lived as other members of the family but he did marry a woman named Laura Elizabeth and together they had two sons, Silas and Patrick Wayne. Laura was 37 when Kenneth died, but never remarried, focusing on their children and their company. In addition to those efforts she was a supporter of Prohibition, and was threatened and intimidated by gangsters and bootleggers, but never backed down from her convictions.

issue_credits.name: Batman vs. Robin, Part 1: The Haunting of Wayne Manor

name: Kenneth Wayne

deck: Father of Thomas Wayne and Grandfather to Bruce Wayne as well as the creator of Wayne Tech and Wayne Corp
description: Patrick Wayne is the father of Thomas Wayne and grandfather to Bruce Wayne. He is the eldest son of Kenneth and Elizabeth Wayne. His father developed Wayne Chemical, but died at a fairly young age leaving the fortune to his 37-year-old wife Laura Wayne. Laura was a shrewd businesswoman and heavily involved in the Prohibition movement, while raising their infant son. Patrick inherited the family business upon his mother's death. He was the creator of Wayne Tech which helped support both World Wars. Later, he would combine the Wayne resources to create Wayne Corp. He worked closely with his brother Silas Wayne.

deck: Clint Barton's girlfriend-turned-wife in the Ultimate continuity.
description:
Origin

Laura was Clint Barton (Hawkeye)'s girlfriend and later wife. The two of them had two children not much later.

Creation

Laura Barton was created by Mark Miller and Bryan Hitch and first appeared in The Ultimates 2 issue 2 (2005). She has solely appeared in the alternate reality 1610, known as the Ultimate Universe.

Major Story Arcs

Death

As part of Loki's plot to undermine the Ultimates and tear the team apart from the inside, Laura and the kids were shot and killed by Black Widow whom turned out to be a traitor whom worked for the Liberators.

Though Hawkeye later avenged her by sending an arrow through the Black Widow's skull, Laura's death affected him greatly, causing him to fall into a depressed state and don a new, edgier persona.

Other Media

Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015)

In the Avengers: Age of Ultron film, Clint Barton reveals that he owns his own farm land, and that he is married to a woman named Laura. They have two children, and a third on the way.

Laura is played by Linda Cardellini.
name: Laura Barton
